cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with a data structure problem of storing correlated files with minimal memory usage and fast decoding time. The focus is on compressing Markov chains, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of compressing the files and empirical entropy. Machine learning (cs.LG) is relevant as Markov chains are commonly used in this field. The paper also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) in terms of counting the number of length-$n$ walks on a graph. Finally, the paper mentions the Dictionary problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
